	text = text.replace("It is the most wonderful sound in the world!", "这是世界上最美妙的声音！");
	text = text.replace("And the women who come after, so hot and bothered they don\'t even wait for you to clean the entrails off before jumping your bones? Glorious.", "追随而来的女人们，如此热辣令人苦恼，她们甚至不等你清理干净内脏就要开干？荣耀啊。");
	text = text.replace("But it gets boring, too.", "但是事情也渐渐变得枯燥。");
	text = text.replace("How many fights has it been?", "已经发生多少场战斗？");
	text = text.replace("You can\'t count. How many challenges?", "你数不清了。有过多少挑战？");
	text = text.replace("You can\'t even name a single one.", "你甚至连一次都说不出。");
	text = text.replace(/Not a single one! (.*?), (.*?), and (.*?) all agree: you\'re just too good\./, "一次都没有！$1，$2，和 $3 都同意，是你太优秀了。");
	text = text.replace("And they\'re pretty good, too, if you\'re being honest.", "要说实话的话他们也同样很棒。");
	text = text.replace("All four of you agree, though: you shall depart the arenas and forge a champion\'s spirit across the whole world.", "不过你们四个都同意：你们应该离开竞技场在整个世界塑造冠军之魂。");
	text = text.replace("The gladiators have some proclivities for the opulent, particularly for scented baths and jewelry that spells their names, so be prepared to pay a tidy sum for each as you finance their lavish lifestyles outside the comfort of the city states.", "角斗士们有一些奢侈的癖好，特别是香薰浴和刻有他们名字的珠宝首饰，所以当你为他们在舒适的城邦之外的奢华生活方式提供资金时，请准备好为他们支付一笔可观的费用。");
	text = text.replace("And so it will be.", "事实也会如此。");
	text = text.replace("Your three solid, but not all-time great fighting buddies will display their martial prowess, and you will be matched with a new challenge: learning how to manage warriors (who are not at your level) and their needs.", "你的三个坚实有力但不总是伟大的战斗伙伴将展现他们的武力，而你也将面临一项新的挑战：学习如何管理战士（和你们不是一个水平的）和他们的需求。");

//lone_wolf_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You walk the stands of a jousting arena.", "你走在竞技场的看台上。");
	text = text.replace("Moldy fruits and vegetables litter the floor.", "发霉的水果和蔬菜散落在地板上。");
	text = text.replace("Dried blood freckles the seats.", "干枯的血液使得座位布满斑点。");
	text = text.replace("And silence fills the air.", "空气中充满了寂静。");
	text = text.replace("When you sit, the wood of the place seems to groan in unison as though discomfited by the haunt of a rare visitor.", "在你坐着的时候，这地方的树木似乎在齐声呻吟，仿佛被一个罕见的访客的出没所困扰。");
	text = text.replace("In your hands is a note.", "你手里拿着一张纸条。");
	text = text.replace("\'Looking fer hardy men, knowledge of the sword pref\'rred but all welcome.\'", "“寻找强壮的人，懂得如何用剑的人优先。”");
	text = text.replace("It is an old note, its purpose long since served.", "这是一张旧纸条，它的目的很久以前就达到了。");
	text = text.replace("But what draws your eye is the price offered to the task: more crowns than you could muster in five tournaments.", "但是吸引你眼球的是这项工作的所得到的报酬比你在五场锦标赛获得冠军还要多。");
	text = text.replace("If this is the coin to be earned, then to hell with the jousts and the sparring.", "如果仅仅是要赚硬币的话，干嘛还要去打拳击和格斗呢。");
	text = text.replace("But you\'re not one to suit up for some other captain\'s orders.", "但是你并不是一个听从队长的命令的人。");
	text = text.replace("With all that you\'ve earned over the years you imagine you could start your own mercenary band just fine.", "这些年来，你赚了不少钱，你想象着可以组建一支自己的雇佣兵团。");

//manhunters_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("Constant conflict between nomads, city states, and vagabonds makes for good business: deserters, criminals, prisoners of war, and indebted alike flee across the land, and you with manacle in hand give chase.", "游牧民族、城邦和流浪汉之间不断的冲突意味着有好生意：逃兵、罪犯、战俘和负债者逃过了这片土地，而你手持镣铐追捕他们。");
	text = text.replace("Despite the barren wastes upon which they rule, the Southern Realms are home to large and ever shifting populations which makes personhood itself a resource worth harvesting.", "尽管他们统治着贫瘠的荒芜之地，但南方王国却是数目众多且不断流动的人们的家园，这使得人本身成为一种值得收获的资源。");
	text = text.replace("The riverlike flow of persons is as natural an economy as any raw material.", "河水般流动的人们和原料一样都是自然经济。");
	text = text.replace("Prisoners of war make up the bulk of your outfit, beaten men who must submit to and fight for another force: your own.", "战俘占了你很大一部分构成，战败之人必须服从并为另一股势力战斗：你自己的。");
	text = text.replace("Criminals and general riff raff fill in here and there, easy pickings from smaller villages who don\'t have the means to handle their resident reprobates.", "罪犯和普通的流氓到处都是，他们很容易从那些无法处理这些堕落的居民的小村落里挑选出来。");
	text = text.replace("And then there are the indebted... hellfire-doomed souls who must work their way back into the Gilder\'s gleam, and find salvation through blood, sweat, and tears.", "还有那些负债者…地狱之火诅咒的灵魂必须通过努力才能回到镀金者的金光沐浴中，并通过鲜血、汗水和泪水找到救赎。");
	text = text.replace("While most must work as laborers, you favor pressing them into your company.", "尽管大部分人要成为工人，你还是喜欢把他们编入自己的战队里。");
	text = text.replace(/The indebted will not protest, for even the priests state it must be within the Gilder\'s sublime vision that they will find penitence in the (.*?)\./, "负债者不会抗议，因为即使是牧师也会说，他们一定会在镀金者的崇高愿景中，他们会找到忏悔就在 $1。");

//militia_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("Hunt down bandits. Ward off raiders.", "追捕土匪。抵御掠夺者。");
	text = text.replace("Trap wolves attacking the farmsteads.", "诱捕攻击农场的狼群。");
	text = text.replace("All in a militiaman\'s work.", "这些全是民兵团的工作。");
	text = text.replace("And if more is asked then there is simply more to answer.", "而且如果你问到底要干多少活，这个答案只会越问越多。");
	text = text.replace(/All to keep your home of (.*?) safe\./, "所有的这一切只是为了保卫你的家园 $1 的安全。");
	text = text.replace("When a nobleman called on you, you and a group of ad hoc fighters took to the field in a battle between highborn.", "当一个贵族召见你的时候，你和你临时组成的新手战士们被带上了贵族之间的战场。");
	text = text.replace("You didn\'t know their names or their quarry, only that one mustered you and your men to the field. And so there you went.", "你不知道他们的贵族称号也不知道他们的目标，你只知道一个人把你和你的人集合带向了战场。");
	text = text.replace("Unfortunately, a lowborn man with spear and shield is little more than a peasant with misgivings of warriorship.", "就是这样。不幸的是即使一个出身卑贱的男人即使拿上了盾牌和长矛也不过是比一个懦弱胆怯的农民好那么一点点。");
	text = text.replace("Your militia was used to hold a contingent of enemy knights in place while your own side\'s archers rained hell from above, hitting knight and peasant alike.", "你的民兵团当时被派去阻挡一支敌人的骑士队伍，你不知道的是迎来的不只是敌人的骑士还有己方弓手的漫天箭雨，这箭雨不仅击中了敌人的骑士还有你手下无辜的民兵。");
	text = text.replace("After the battle, you and your men fled the fields for good.", "在这场战斗过后你和你的人永远的逃离了这片战场。");
	text = text.replace("You took up arms as sellswords and swore to one another by blood pact that you\'d never have a highborn in your company.", "你和你的人将自己武装的如同佣兵一样，并且彼此用血发誓你们永远不会让一个贵族与你们为伍。");
	text = text.replace("A mercenary band of motley men and that is that.", "一群普普通通的人组成的雇佣兵团，仅此而已。");

//paladins_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You knew the game well, and like any good game you got burned out on the rules and the rule setters.", "你对这种游戏很熟悉，就像任何让你被规则和规则制定者搞的灰头土脸焦头烂额的游戏一样。");
	text = text.replace("Oaths for this, Oaths for that.", "这里一个誓言，那里一个誓言。");
	text = text.replace("All you knew is you never got to hold Young Anselm\'s skull, and last you saw some Oathbringer had stolen off with the lad\'s preeminent jaw.", "你只知道你绝对不会去持有小安瑟姆的头骨，最后你看到一些誓言使者把那个孩子的颌骨给偷跑了。");
	text = text.replace("Leaving the Oathtakers was the best decision you ever made, if only to preserve what little sanity you had left.", "离开宣誓者真是你这辈子最正确的决定，你总算还能保持那么一丁点儿理智。");
	text = text.replace("Unfortunately, the faithful have a strong nose for the apostate\'s scent.", "不幸的是，那些忠实信徒仿佛总是能闻到叛教者的味道。");
	text = text.replace(/When you opened the door this morning it was like looking at two piles of shite some prankster kid had left you: (.*?) and (.*?), in the flesh\./, "当你今天早上打开大门时你仿佛看到一个恶作剧的孩子拉的两坨屎：$1 和 $2，虽然他们是肉做的。");
	text = text.replace("The former an older man who simply never shook his beliefs, and the latter a talented squire who reminds you of yourself.", "前者是一位从来就没有动摇过信仰的老人，后者是一个像你自己一样潜质很好的扈从。");
	text = text.replace("No doubt the more mawkish talker, it was the younger lad who made his plea: the Oathtakers need a man familiar with the land to help them around, completing quests and oaths.", "一通无病呻吟的屁话，那个年轻人恳求道：宣誓者需要一位熟悉地形的人来帮助他们，完成任务和兑现誓言。");
	text = text.replace("You shut the door only to find the older man\'s foot in it.", "你正准备摔门而去却发现那个老人把脚卡在门上不让你关门。");
	text = text.replace("He held up a pile of gold, and your nose must have wrinkled or wiggled because both men lit up.", "他拿着一大堆金币，你的鼻子一定在因为钱的味道扭曲着因为两个人都面露喜色。");
	text = text.replace("Now, you\'re only going along because times are tough, and because mercenary work – even under the guise of religious duty – can make some outstanding coin.", "现在，你之所以这么做，只是因为时局艰难，也因为雇佣兵工作－就算披上宗教责任的外衣－还是能为你挣到一些硬币的。");
	text = text.replace("And if someone is willing to bankroll you into such an opulent task, then so be it.", "既然有人愿意出资让你接这个大有赚头的任务，那也没啥不可以的。");
	text = text.replace("There is only one condition: you will take the Oath of Captaincy, which means all the battling and rough roading will be done by others.", "只有一个条件：你将宣誓成为队长，这意味着所有的战斗和艰难的道路将由他人完成。");
	text = text.replace("Without pause, the Oathtakers agree, and then they show you Young Anselm\'s skull.", "丝毫没有迟疑，宣誓者同意了，然后他们拿出了小安瑟姆的颅骨展示给你。");
	text = text.replace(/You\'ve lost touch with the organization, but seeing that lad\'s dumb dome still brings a stir in your heart\. (.*?) nods\./, "你与组织失去联系已经很久了，但看着这个孩子无法合口的穹顶你还是感到心底一阵悸动。$1 点点头。");
	text = text.replace("Let us scour these lands for the honorable, and be diligent in our tasks, and may we ever make Young Anselm whole again from the rat bastard Oathbringers who broke him!", "让我们搜寻这片土地寻找荣耀，勤于我们的责任，并且愿我们能让小安瑟姆从那些毁了他的卑鄙杂种誓言使者的手中合整回来！");

//raiders_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("After you and your party killed half of them, the villagers finally submitted.", "在你和你的部队杀掉了一半的村民之后村民们终于投降了。");
	text = text.replace("A white flag was raised, and they offered parlay which you were happy to grant.", "一面白色的小旗从中升起并且村民们还要求停战，你很乐意答应他们。");
	text = text.replace("In a single line they walked out to the town square where they had been holding a festival.", "村民们一字排开的走向他们之前举行节日庆典的城镇广场。");
	text = text.replace("Jewels and treasures filled their arms and they dumped the goods where you stood, boot atop the smashed skull of their mayor.", "村民们一个一个的把怀中的珠宝和财宝放到了你脚下被打碎的镇长的脑袋旁边。");
	text = text.replace(/Your vanguard of (.*?), (.*?), (.*?) and (.*?) kept careful watch of the ceremony like buzzards watching a slow death\./, "你的先锋部队 $1，$2，$3 和 $4 小心地看着村民们就像秃鹰看着快死的动物慢慢死去一样。");
	text = text.replace("The last in the line was a monk.", "队伍中最后一个人是个僧侣。");
	text = text.replace("He had no gold or silver on him, but instead spoke to you, his words immediately drawing the weapons of your fellow raiders.", "他的身上没有任何金子或者银子并且还开始对你说话，他的行为立刻让你的手下们掏出了他们的武器。");
	text = text.replace("You allowed him to speak, and he spoke at length about the old gods and how the treasures of the heavens superseded all of that which terra could offer.", "你允许了他说话，但是他却开始谈论古老的神明是怎么被天堂取代的并且如果你相信了天堂又会有怎样的财富等待着你。");
	text = text.replace("You told him his death was written by that wagging chin of his.", "你告诉他他这张灵巧的嘴只会早就自己的死亡之后。");
	text = text.replace("The monk pursed his lips.", "僧侣赶紧闭上了嘴但是又慢慢说到。");
	text = text.replace("Alright, then if you want gold, depart these silly games.", "好吧，好吧如果你真的想要财富的话就放弃这种无聊愚蠢的游戏吧。");
	text = text.replace("This raiding and pillaging, it is all worthless compared to the treasures of the south.", "这种掠夺和抢劫根本比不上南方财富的哪怕一点点。");
	text = text.replace("The nobles won\'t have you in their armies, but they are forever in need of mercenaries and rarely have the time or luxury of choosing where these hired fighters come from.", "贵族首领们肯定不会让你加入他们的军队但是他们会很乐意雇佣一队佣兵并且他们才不会用他们宝贵的时间研究这队雇佣兵是从哪里来的。");
	text = text.replace("You\'d make all the crowns you\'d ever want.", "你将会得到你梦寐以求的财富的。");
	text = text.replace("Come south, raiders, and be sublimated into sellswords.", "去南方吧，掠夺者，去作为以队佣兵生活吧。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) demands the monk\'s head, but you stay the execution\./, "$1 想要把这个僧侣的头砍下来但是你把这个处决决定先保存了下来。");
	text = text.replace("Instead, you take the crafty monk at his word.", "相反，你听信了这个狡猾的僧侣的话。");
	text = text.replace("You\'ve long heard of southern riches and the travels of adventurous swords for hire.", "你早就听说过了南方的财富和冒险者被雇佣来战斗的故事。");
	text = text.replace(/You decide to venture south - so long as the monk comes with\. (.*?) protests, but you won\'t have it\./, "你决定去南方，并且带上了这个僧侣和你一起。$1 对于这个带上僧侣这个决定是抗拒的但是你根本没听。");
	text = text.replace("If this pale little shit of a monk is your lucky charm to a new life, then it would be an affront to the old gods to leave him be.", "因为如果这个小白脸僧侣是你去往新生活的幸运护符的话，杀掉他就是对古老神明的侮辱了。");
	text = text.replace(/The raider storms off, but (.*?), (.*?) and (.*?) have no qualms about following you\./, "其他掠夺者们鸟兽一样散去，但是 $1，$2 和 $3 对于跟随你的领导没有任何异议。");
	text = text.replace("The rest of the war party returns north, a split in the loot being made.", "其他的掠夺者们返回了北方并且分掉了掠夺的财富。");
	text = text.replace("What remains of the village is left behind to recover, rebuild, and make new goods for stronger tribes to come and take for themselves.", "留下来的村庄还需要重建和回复并且还会有新的陌生部落前来拿走他们想要的财富。");

//rangers_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("Despite tales of lone hungry hunters just looking to feed a family, poachers often work in teams and create whole businesses out of the trade of stolen furs and meats.", "尽管有很多故事中说猎人都是一个人孤独地在养活他的家庭，但是现实中偷猎者经常有组织的成群结队的工作，并且建立起一整套销售渠道来贩卖他们偷来的毛皮和肉。");
	text = text.replace(/But as your local lord, (.*?), became increasingly annoyed with poachers hunting in his woods, most of the surrounding groups of hunters were caught, mutilated, and hanged\./, "但当地贵族首领 $1 对偷猎者在他的森林中进行狩猎感到越来越恼火，周围大部分猎人团体被抓到不是切手就是送上绞架。");
	text = text.replace(/With just yourself, (.*?), (.*?), and (.*?) remaining, a decision had to be made - how to make a living when all you know is how to use a bow\?/, "只剩下了你和 $1，$2，和 $3 幸存了下来，但是现在的问题是－如果你所会的所有技巧知识只是拉弓放箭的话怎么才能活下来？");
	text = text.replace("It was deciced to turn your collective talents to mercenary work, and you were promptly elected captain of the outfit.", "根据大家集体讨论之后一致决定接受作为雇佣兵的工作，并且你很快被选为了队长。");
	text = text.replace("It was decided to turn your collective talents to mercenary work, and you were promptly elected captain of the outfit.", "根据大家集体讨论之后一致决定接受作为雇佣兵的工作，并且你很快被选为了队长。");
	text = text.replace("You have the sharpest eyes of us all.", "在我们之中你眼最尖。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) said, and (.*?) agreed, though tempered it\./, "$1 说并且 $2 也同意他的意见并说道。");
	text = text.replace("And you are, of course, easily the worst shot of the group.", "不仅你的眼睛最尖并且你的射击技巧还是我们之中最差的。");
	text = text.replace("Don\'t whip for that one, CAPTAIN, ha-haaa!", "别因为我说了这句话就惩罚我哦，“队长”，哈哈哈！");
	text = text.replace("Certainly, your merry band of poachers brings unique talents to the table - your men prefer to travel light, but they are quick on their feet, good shots with a bow and experts in scouting to avoid unfavorable engagements.", "当然这队快乐的偷猎者队伍还会为你带来独特的天赋－你的人喜欢轻装上阵，并且他们的腿脚很快，弓箭射的很好，还是侦察方面的大师从而避免不必要的战斗。");

//southern_quickstart_intro_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You could have stayed home. Never left town.", "你本可以留在家乡。从未离开过小镇。");
	text = text.replace("Just lived out your days laboring for some Vizier.", "为维齐尔干活度日。");
	text = text.replace("Instead, you took up the sword, scrounged what little money the Gilder had shone upon you, and started a band of mercenaries.", "然而，你拿起宝剑，搜刮镀金者施舍给你的些许钱财，并组建了一支雇佣军。");
	text = text.replace("Life as a Crownling has taken you places that most others never see.", "作为逐币者的日子让你见识了绝大部分人从未见过的地方。");
	text = text.replace("In a sense, you\'ve carved open doors and avenues through violence.", "从某种意义上，你已经通过暴力开凿出了自己的门路。");
	text = text.replace("But the years have slowly weighed down your neck with a nasty truth: you\'re barely a step above being a brigand.", "然而这些年来你慢慢发现一个难堪的事实：你不比一个强盗好多少。");
	text = text.replace("You get hired by locals to do simple things for simple pay and then sent on your way.", "你被当地人用浅薄的报酬雇佣去处理一些简单的事情然后被派往该去的地方。");
	text = text.replace(/You want the (.*?) to be bigger than that\./, "你想要 $1 做大做强。");
	text = text.replace("You want your company shown to the Vizier\'s offices, you want it to gain the glory it deserves, and maybe you want it to even travel north to faraway lands.", "你想要你的战队出现在维齐尔的办公室里，你想让它获得它应得的荣耀，也许甚至想北上遥远之地。");
	text = text.replace("Hell, maybe in the north they treat a mercenary with respect!", "见鬼，也许在北方他们会很尊重雇佣兵！");
	text = text.replace("Of course, it won\'t be easy.", "当然，这一切并不容易。");
	text = text.replace("You\'ve just a few men on hand.", "你手头只有几个人。");
	text = text.replace(/But those men are (.*?), (.*?), and (.*?), the finest fighters you\'ve ever known\./, "但这些人是 $1，$2，和 $3，你所知最好的战士。");
	text = text.replace(/With them at your side, the whole world shall come to know the (.*?)!/, "有他们在你身边，全世界都将知晓 $1！");

//trader_intro_event.nut
