	text = text.replace(/When this morning you found him gone, it wasn\'t much of a surprise\. (.*?) has deserted the (.*?)\./, "今天早上你发现他走了，这并不奇怪。$1 已经离开了 $2。");
	text = text.replace(/You are troubled to learn that (.*?) seems to have disappeared during the night\./, "当你得知 $1 似乎在夜里失踪时，你感到很不安。");
	text = text.replace("After questioning the others and ensuring he hadn\'t simply stepped behind a nearby boulder to relieve his bowels, you call out a search.", "在询问了其他人并确定他不是简单地走到附近的一块大石头后面去方便之后，你发起了一场搜查。");
	text = text.replace(/Thinking that perhaps (.*?) had been taken by treachery, kidnapped for ransom, or fallen afoul of some beast, you and the brothers spent several hours searching the area and calling his name\./, "你和兄弟们以为 $1 可能是被叛国者绑架，被绑架者勒索，或是与某个野兽作对，就花了几个小时搜索这个地区，呼喊着他的名字。");
	text = text.replace(/Then (.*?) finally suggests that (.*?) is not missing at all, but has deserted you all\./, "这时 $1 终于表示 $2 根本就没失踪，而是已经抛弃了你们所有人离开了。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s been griping about the company lately, but I guess he hid it from you, sir, so he\'d have a chance to slip away unseen.", "他最近一直在抱怨战队的事，但我想他是瞒着你说的，先生，这样他就有机会偷偷溜走了。");
	text = text.replace("Restraining the urge to give the bearer of bad news a solid box about the ears, you ask why he didn\'t come forward earlier, but the brother has no answer.", "你抑制住了想给坏消息传递者一记耳光的冲动，问他为什么不早点说出来，但他没有回答。");
	text = text.replace(/You never figured (.*?) for the type to desert, but when the dawn comes and he\'s nowhere to be seen you realize you were being naive\./, "你从来没有想过 $1 是会叛逃的人，但是当黎明来临的时候，他却不见了，你意识到你太天真了。");
	text = text.replace("On every march he had been falling farther and farther behind, and every time you gave the order to break camp, he was last to gather his gear and start walking.", "每一次行军他都落在后面越来越远的地方，每次你命令他出发他总是最后一个收拾好装备才走。");
	text = text.replace("His equipment had also begun to look ratty.", "他的装备也开始显得破烂不堪。");
	text = text.replace("Though he kept his thoughts to himself, in retrospect his sour looks and disinterest in his comrades made it obvious he wasn\'t happy with the direction the company has been heading in lately.", "尽管他把自己的想法藏在心里，但回想起来，他那副酸楚的表情和对战友们的漠不关心，显然表明他对战队最近的发展方向并不满意。");
	text = text.replace("You sound out the other men and discover discontent is on the rise generally.", "你开始试探其他人，发现不满情绪在普遍上升。");
	text = text.replace(/Keep the men well fed and watered like any beast, and make sure they get paid on time, and hopefully (.*?) will be the last to flee in the night\./, "让这些人像野兽一样吃好、喝好，确保他们按时得到报酬，希望 $1 会是在夜里最后一个逃跑的人。");
	text = text.replace(/You do not know if it was the low pay, the threat of dismemberment, the forced marches in icy rain, the foul language and coarse food, the abuse at the hands of his brothers, the small children throwing stones, the cold wind or the sleepless nights, but (.*?) has grown more and more unhappy this last while until apparently he gave up on the mercenary life altogether\./, "你不知道是因为工资低，差点残疾的危机还是在冰冷的雨中被迫行军或者人们粗鄙的语言和粗劣难以入口食物，他战友们的虐待，孩子们冲他扔的石头，凌冽的寒风，还是一个又一个不眠之夜，但 $1 在最后这段时间变得越来越不快乐，直到他明显地完全放弃了雇佣兵生涯。");
	text = text.replace("Don\'t know what he has to complain about.", "我不知道他有什么可抱怨的。");
	text = text.replace("Everything seems right normal to me.", "我觉得一切都很正常。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) says when hearing about the whole thing. (.*?) has chosen the open road over the (.*?)\. At least he had the decency to tell you in person that he decided to leave - although, thinking about it, perhaps it was just to collect his remaining pay in person\./, "$1 听到这件事情后说。$2 选择了其他道路，而不是 $3。至少他很有礼貌的当面告诉你他决定离开－尽管，考虑到这一点，也许只是为了当面收回他剩余的工资。");
	text = text.replace(/Lately, (.*?) had begun to take long walks in the evening when the day\'s work was done\./, "最近，$1 开始在白天的工作结束后的晚上散步。");
	text = text.replace("Though his habit of wandering off alone wasn\'t exactly safe, you could think of no reason to stop him when he wasn\'t needed in camp.", "虽然他独自游荡的习惯并不十分安全，但你想不出任何理由在营地不需要他的时候阻止他。");
	text = text.replace(/However, the more hardships the company faced, the longer these walks became, until one morning (.*?) did not return at all\./, "然而，战队面临的困难越多，他们走的路就越长，直到有一天早上 $1 再也没有回来。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) has deserted the (.*?)\. It\'s probably for the best\./, "$1 已离开 $2。这可能是最好的结果吧。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) has been especially moody of late, spending all his off hours fondling an old throwing knife, a blade in such poor condition it more closely resembled a bit of scrap iron than a proper weapon\./, "$1 最近特别喜怒无常，他把所有的空闲时间都花在摆弄一把旧的飞刀上，一把状况很差的刀，它更像是一块废铁，而不是一件合适的武器。");
	text = text.replace("He spent the previous evening throwing it at the bole of a dead tree, each time rising with a groan to retrieve it and walking back several yards to squat down and throw it again, well into the night.", "前一天晚上，他把它扔向一棵枯树的树干上，每次起身时都唉声叹气着把它捡起来，然后走回几码远的地方蹲下来，再把它扔回去，一直扔到深夜。");
	text = text.replace("Clearly he was unhappy with the recent setbacks the company has faced, at this morning he mustered the courage to enter your tent and explain that he\'ll be leaving the company to seek his fortune elsewhere.", "显然，他对战队最近遇到的挫折很不高兴，今天早上，他鼓足勇气走进你的帐篷，向你解释说，他将离开战队到别处去寻找他的财富。");

//dismiss_injured_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?)\'s injuries proved too much: the man didn\'t die, but in your mind he might as well have for he was no longer fit for combat\./, "$1的伤势实在太重了：那个人没有死，但是在你看来，他还是死了的好，因为他已经不适合战斗了。");
	text = text.replace("You let him go.", "你让他走了。");
	text = text.replace("While this may have been an altruistic move that spared the sellsword\'s life, the rest of the company doesn\'t see it the same way.", "虽然这可能是一个拯救这个佣兵生命的举动，但战队的其他人不这么认为。");
	text = text.replace("All they see is that one injury is all it took for you to cut a man loose.", "他们看到的是，你只因受了一次伤，就能够把一个人解雇掉。");
	text = text.replace("Now they worry that if they get wounded you might do the same to them, like a selfish man ridding himself of a lame horse.", "现在她们担心，如果他们受伤了，你也会对他们做同样的事情，就像自私的人骑着瘸腿的马一样。");

//dismiss_legend_event.nut
	text = text.replace("The man you let go wasn\'t just a part of the company: he was a legend.", "这个你解雇的男人不只是战队的一个佣兵而已：他曾是一个传奇。");
	text = text.replace(/Many knew (.*?)\'s name, not just yourself and a few mercenaries, and having him leave is akin to firing a heroic general before a war-ending battle\./, "很多人都知道 $1的大名，不仅仅是你和一些雇佣兵知道，现在解雇他就如在战斗结束前解雇一个英勇的将军一样。");
	text = text.replace("The decision, naturally, does not go over well with the rest of the sellswords.", "这个决定，很自然的，在其他佣兵之中反响不是很好。");

//dismiss_veteran_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/It was a tough decision, but you had to cut (.*?) loose\./, "这是一个艰难的决定，但是必须解雇 $1。");
	text = text.replace("However, it appears you should have consulted the rest of the men first for none of them are happy with your choice.", "不管怎样，看起来你应该先和其他人商量一下，因为他们都不满意你的选择。");
	text = text.replace("The mercenary had been in the company long enough to make friends, and even those who weren\'t close to him still felt as though his place on the battlefield ensured their own safety.", "这个雇佣兵在团队中待的时间足够长足以交到很多朋友，就算那些不是和他很熟的人也感觉他在战场上的位置保证了他们的安全。");

//helped_caravan_event.nut
	text = text.replace("The caravan\'s lead merchant comes to you with thanks for saving him.", "商队的头领来到你跟前，感谢你救了他。");
	text = text.replace("Naturally, he provides more than just words: a number of goods are given, some of which will be of use.", "当然，他提供的远远超过语言文字：赠送了一些物品，其中一些是能派上用场的。");
	text = text.replace("Thank you, traveler, thank you!", "谢谢你，旅行者，谢谢你！");
	text = text.replace("The caravan\'s merchant master clasps his hands and shakes them up and down as though to thank you and the old gods alike.", "商队的商人头领紧握双手，上下摇动着，好像要感谢你和古老的神一样。");
	text = text.replace(/He also says thanks with material goods, providing the (.*?) with an assortment of rewards straight off the wagons\./, "他还用货品感谢你，给 $1 提供各种各样直接从载重货车上拿下来的奖励。");
	text = text.replace("It is rare for strangers in this world to see one another in good grace, but even a wily merchant understands that if he is saved from total annihilation then perhaps he best reward his saviors.", "在这个世界上，陌生人能彼此友善的相遇是稀有的，但即使是一个狡猾的商人也明白，如果他从彻底消失中悲拯救出来，那么他最好回报他的救主。");
	text = text.replace("The caravan lightens its load by rewarding you with a number of goods.", "商队通过奖励你一些货物来减轻他的负载。");
	text = text.replace("Had you not arrived this caravan surely would have met doom.", "如果你没有来，这支商队肯定会遭殃。");
	text = text.replace("It rewards you properly for your impromptu \'services.\'", "这是对你及时的“服务”即兴的奖励。");
	text = text.replace("Oh by any higher power which may or may not exist to you, but whatever it is, it now reigns over me!", "噢，以一种更高的力量，这种力量对你来说可能存在，也可能不存在，但不管它是什么，它现在支配着我!");
	text = text.replace("The merchant is clearly in shock.", "商人显然处于震惊状态。");
	text = text.replace("And, like any disturbed peddler, he immediately goes to the one thing he knows how to do.", "像任何一个不安的小贩一样，他会立刻去做他知道该怎么做的事情。");
	text = text.replace("Look, we\'ve goods to offer, how about these?", "瞧，我们有货可提供，这些怎么样？");
	text = text.replace("Tokens of our gratitude, free of charge.", "接受我们感激的谢礼，免费的。");
	text = text.replace("Though the battle is over, the hysteria of the saved merchants is just as loud as the carnage which has just passed.", "尽管战斗已经结束，被拯救的商人们的歇斯底里还是和刚刚过去的大屠杀一样响亮。");
	text = text.replace("Sellswords, sellswords! Our saviors!", "佣兵，佣兵！我们的救主！");
	text = text.replace("Suddenly, you find the merchants swarming with goods as thanks for saving them.", "突然间，你发现商人们都在感谢你的救援。");

//oathtakers_confrontation_event.nut
	text = text.replace("\'We\'ll be seeing you someday,\' they said, spoken softly like old friends, but they meant it, meant it in only the way enemies can.", "“我们还会再见面的”，他们说道，说得很温和就像老朋友一样，但是他们在玩真的，这是只有仇敌才会有的一种认真。");
	text = text.replace("Them. The Oathbringers. Now standing before you in glinting steel, chins up and weapons readied, a salient of hate, manifest from the untimely demise of Young Anselm.", "他们，那些誓言使者。现在就站在你的面前，身披闪亮的铠甲，趾高气昂并且武器出鞘，突显的仇恨，显示小安瑟姆死的真不是时候。");
	text = text.replace(/You thought you would find them in much larger number, but now only two stand wishing to confront the (.*?)\. One steps forward\./, " 你本以为他们会人数更多一些，但是现在只有两个人在面对 $1。向前跨出一步。");
	text = text.replace("You see Young Anselm\'s jawbone dangling from his neck. The Oathbringer nods.", "你看见小安瑟姆的下颌骨在他的脖子上晃悠。那个誓者使者点点头。");
	text = text.replace("I knew it the day we departed that it were only a matter of time until we saw each other again.", "我们分开那天我就知道再次遇到你就只是个时间问题。");
	text = text.replace("I can see you have been fighting many a battle, as have we.", "我能看出来你们一直在打仗，我们也是一样。");
	text = text.replace("It is clear that Young Anselm\'s prophecies bore such weight that this world would see us brought together one final time, not robbed of the ceremony on account of some brigand or greenskin.", "很明显小安瑟姆的预言影响深远以至于整个世界都能见证我们最终某天宿命的相遇，考虑到那些强盗和绿皮怪物我们就不搞仪式了。");
	text = text.replace("You and I both have been shielded by fate, clothed in the invincibility of one very certain inevitability.", "你和我都被命运保护着，披上了一种必然的不可战胜的外衣。");
	text = text.replace("Oathtakers. Oathbringers. Let us settle this schism once and for all.", "宣誓者。誓言使者。我们来一劳永逸地解决这个分歧吧。");
	text = text.replace("As Young Anselm decreed, choose your finest fighters, and we shall see which of us are most deserving of upholding the Oaths!", "接受小安瑟姆的裁决，选出你最强壮的战士，让我们来看看我们之间谁更有资格维护这神圣的誓言！");
	
	text = text.replace("The Oathbringers stand before you, waiting for you to pick your champions.", "誓者使者站在你面前，等待你挑选冠军。");
	text = text.replace(/You\'ve already chosen (.*?) and (.*?) to fight\./, "你已经选择了 $1 和 $2 去战斗。");
	text = text.replace("Is there another who shall help reclaim Young Anselm\'s jawbone?", "有没有其他人可以帮助夺回小安瑟姆的下颌骨？");
	text = text.replace("stands ready to fight.", "随时准备战斗。");
	text = text.replace("Who shall join him?", "谁能加入他？");
	
	text = text.replace("Two bodies on the ground, and a weight off your shoulders.", "两具躯体倒在地上，你总算卸下了心头的大石头。");
	text = text.replace("But… you thought it would be different.", "不过…你觉得一切都会有所不同。");
	text = text.replace("Not that you are displeased with the results, such that the Oathbringers are no more, but there\'s something amiss.", "你并非对结果不满意，毕竟誓言使者已经不再对你构成威胁，但是你还是怅然若失。");
	text = text.replace("It is almost as if you put out a fire that threatened your home, only to realize those flames were the only warmth you had in a world of cold.", "这就好像你扑灭了一场即将烧毁你房子的大火，结果却发现你亲手扑灭的大火竟然是你在这个冰冷世界上唯一的温暖和慰藉。");
	text = text.replace("Good riddance.", "很好的解脱。");
	text = text.replace("One of your men says and spits on the corpses.", "你的一个手下这样说道并朝尸体吐了一口唾沫。");
	text = text.replace("Staring at the dead, you realize you had become addicted to the hunt, addicted to the challenge, addicted to being strong.", "盯着尸体，你意识到你开始沉迷于狩猎，沉迷于挑战，沉迷于不断变强。");
	text = text.replace("You weren\'t encumbered by a threat.", "你不会被一个威胁所拖累。");
	text = text.replace(/You were weighted with purpose, and now it is gone\. (.*?) leans down and picks up Young Anselm\'s jawbone and hands it over\./, "你曾经为了目标而战，而现在你已经迷失了。$1 弯腰捡起了小安瑟姆的下颌骨并且递给你。");
	text = text.replace("You take it and piece it to Young Anselm\'s skull.", "你拿着它，把这部分拼接到小安瑟姆的颅骨上。");
	text = text.replace("It fits with ease, almost as if even in its decay it had no reason to separate.", "很轻松就拼接上去了，就好像长年的腐蚀磨损都没能使它们分开过。");
	text = text.replace("The men cheer. They cheer the Oathtakers.", "大家欢呼起来。他们欢呼着宣誓者。");
	text = text.replace("They cheer your name.", "他们欢呼着你的名字。");
	text = text.replace("And they cheer for Young Anselm who in death has finally been made whole again.", "他们为小安瑟姆欢呼在死后终于能被合为一体。");
	text = text.replace("You take one last look at the Oathbringers and nod.", "你最后一次看向誓言使者们并且点了点头。");
	text = text.replace("They had a purpose, sure, but now it is fulfilled.", "他们也有目标，显然如此，但现在他们的目标已经完成了。");
	text = text.replace("May the old gods have mercy on their heathen souls.", "愿古神怜悯他们这些异教者的灵魂。");
	
	text = text.replace("You stare in disbelief as your chosen fighters go down.", "你难以置信地看着你选择的战士被打倒在地。");
	text = text.replace("A thought crosses your mind to kill the Oathbringers, but rules are rules and you wouldn\'t dare infringe on Young Anselm\'s oath of proper combat.", "你的大脑里飞快闪过一个念头想要干掉这个誓言使者，但是规矩就是规矩你不敢在一场公平决斗中违背小安瑟姆的誓言。");
	text = text.replace("You watch as an Oathbringer takes up Young Anselm\'s jawbone, presses thumb to mandible, and promptly snaps the relic in half.", "你看着一个誓言使者捡起小安瑟姆的下颌骨，把拇指插进下颚处，然后迅速地把这件圣物掰成两段。");
	text = text.replace("Despite our victory, even we Oathbringers can see that we\'ve both our errors.", "尽管我们赢了，甚至我们誓言使者都能看出来我们都有错误。");
	text = text.replace("So let schism grace schism!", "所以让分歧来解决分歧吧！");
	text = text.replace("Through us we all take on the Oath of Failure, and see unto this world that we find true followers of the Oaths...", "我们立下的誓言失败了，并且环顾世界让我们在这个世界上找到真正的追随者…");
	text = text.replace("The Oathbringer stares at you through the broken bones, himself shielded by a dead man\'s decree.", "那个誓言使者的目光从破碎的骨头间穿过盯着你，而他本人却因为已逝者的法令保护而使你徒呼奈何。");
	text = text.replace("When Young Anselm\'s guidance finds fulfillment, only then shall he be made whole again.", "只有小安瑟姆的指引得到了满足，他才能够被拼接成一个整体。");
	text = text.replace("The Oathbringer turns and leaves.", "那个誓言使者转身离开。");
	text = text.replace("Your heart races with ideas of stabbing him in the back, cobbling Anselm\'s remains back together, and completing your ultimate task.", "你的心在不断闪过一个个念头想要在背后给他一刀，把小安瑟姆的遗体拼接完整，并且完成你的终极任务。");
	text = text.replace("But the notion passes.", "但这些念头最终还是全部烟消云散。");
	text = text.replace("To do such a thing would curse you forever with having ruined your firmest beliefs.", "这么做会让你永受诅咒毁掉你最坚定的信念。");
	text = text.replace("You simply watch the Oathbringer go, knowing that the Oaths and all its believers may one day come back together, but it will not be in your lifetime.", "你只是看着那个誓言使者离开，你知道那个誓言和它所有的信徒也许终有一天能重现，但对于你来说已经是此生无望。");

//oathtakers_noble_contracts_event.nut
	text = text.replace("The men come to you with a startling discovery: on the inside cup of Young Anselm\'s brainpan was a tiny, rolled up letter - and its wax stamp bears the mark of a nobleman\'s ring.", "那人给你带来了一个惊人的发现：在小安瑟姆的颅骨内侧有一封小小的，卷起来的信件－它的蜡封上有一枚贵族戒指印章的花纹。");
	text = text.replace("With agreement amongst the men, you tear it open and give it a read.", "在征得大家的同意后，你打开蜡封并且开始阅读。");
	text = text.replace("You find that Young Anselm himself was of high birth, and that he had a writ of Curia in Absentia - or in mercenary parlance, an allowance to enter noble courts.", "你发现小安瑟姆出生血统高贵，并且他持有法庭的缺席令状－或者用佣兵的说法，就是进入贵族法庭的许可。");
	text = text.replace("You look out at the men and say,", "你看向大家并说，");
	text = text.replace("Young Anselm has blessed us all once again!", "小安瑟姆又一次保佑了我们！");
	text = text.replace("While the sensibilities of deracinated sellswords would prevent such scapegraces from ever talking with nobles, much less profaning their delicate stone floors, Young Anselm\'s letter carries a unique marker: anyone who is in his company will also gain the selfsame access, that includes this world or the next.", "那些跟贵族交谈接任务的佣兵们多半成了被灭口的替罪羊，以免亵渎到贵族们圣洁的地板，但是小安瑟姆的信件上有一个独特的记号：这意味着整个队伍中的任何人都将得到一个完全相同的觐见贵族的渠道，而且这个渠道永久有效。");
